    "text": "Over the years, I’ve enjoyed showers in spas, hotels and resorts offering high-tech jets, sauna features and all kinds of fancy shampoos. But none of that compared with the shower I took last week at a store on West 22nd Street in Manhattan.\n\nYes, at the Kohler Experience Center, the fixtures maker offers a free shower right in the showroom, complete with toiletries, robe and slippers. It’s just one of many notable “experiences” brands are offering New Yorkers in an effort to revitalize retail. You could spend the day visiting...  ",
